<section id="homepage">
  <section id="introduction">
    <section>
      Ways We Enjoy Magic Cards is a concise overview of Magic, a popular game that is both addictive and innocent, and operates on so many levels that the discussions almost never end.
    </section>
  
    <section>
      It lists dozens of ways to enjoy Magic's culture (many are free, most are affordable).  While explaining some of the appeal, it hints at how to join in.
    </section>
  </section>
  <%= wwemc_purchase "Let's play the game" %>
  <section id="license">
    <section>
      $2 gets you the book and sends it to (up to) four friends.  You'll all have lifetime access to our weekly updates.
    </section>
  
    <section>
      You'll receive a PDF via email and access to an online edition with links to further information.  Since not everyone can make purchases online, we make one <%= link_to 'chapter', free_book_chapters_path(Book.featured) %> available every day.
    </section>
  </section>
  <%= wwemc_purchase "I have $2!" %>
  <section id="explanation">
    <section>
      Magic: The Gathering was first played 25 years ago.  It rapidly spread, gradually developed, and after a couple big ups and downs, it has surged to a new peak.  There are millions of players in the US and millions more globally.
    </section>
  
    <section>
      Magic is not one game, but a framework for various formats, each of which creates different trends and challenges.  Ways We Enjoy Magic Cards will help you and your loved ones find formats that are fun for every occasion.
    </section>
  </section>
  <%= wwemc_purchase "That's worth more than $2" %>
</section>
